<TITLE> Robinho tells Pele to retract reported drug remarks </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 RIO DE JANEIRO, March 25 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Brazil forward Robinho has demanded that Pele retract remarks he reportedly made last week which insinuated that the Manchester City player took drugs. Robinho added in a statement on his website (www.robinhoofficial.com) that he would take legal action if Pele did not back down. "A formal retraction from Pele will be requested, if what he said was not misinterpreted by the media that published it," the statement said. "And if Pele does not come forward, he will have to deal with his very unfortunate comment in court." The statement added: "Robinho is upset and disappointed at Pele." Robinho was raised at Santos, the same Brazilian club where Pele spent nearly all his career. When he first burst onto the scene as a teenager, Robinho was likened to Pele because of his physique and trickery on the ball
